					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Before I was running the NES at 1/6 the normal clock rate and digitizing the video waveform (so I could get 6x the horizontal resolution). I theorized that the $3x colors would overshoot when the signal was low-pass filtered to the ~6MHz video bandwidth), but when I ran my NES back at full-speed and digitized the waveform, I didn't see any overshoot. So it seems your idea of using the unadjusted chroma square wave amplitudes directly is correct, and my idea of scaling them by 1.27 is not.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

