			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So it seems your idea of using the unadjusted chroma square wave amplitudes directly is correct, and my idea of scaling them by 1.27 is not.</div>
<br />It depends on how the TV user has set the "color" knob. It could be at 1.0, or it could be at 1.27.
<br />
<br />A color TV has five knobs, with the following effects on signal processing: <ul><li>Brightness - luma DC offset </li><li>Contrast - signal gain </li><li>Sharpness - luma high-boost filter gain </li><li>Color - chroma gain </li><li>Tint - chroma phase offset </li></ul></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
